<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Nicolai, Berlin" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" title="Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis, specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per familias, genera, species et varietates disposita atque descripta ab Adrea Gustavo Dahlbom. Chrysis in sensu Linneano" year="1854">Dahlbom (1854</bibRefCitation>
: 122) described 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysis aurifrons" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurifrons">Chrysis aurifrons</taxonomicName>
based on two specimens from the MNHU (found under the name 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysis aurifrons" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurifrons">Chrysis aurifrons</taxonomicName>
Klug) and the Spinola collection (found under the name 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysis integra var. chrysocephala" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="integra" variety="chrysocephala">Chrysis integra var. chrysocephala</taxonomicName>
). The type locality is &quot;Italia, Mus. Spinolae&quot; and &quot;Asia minori teste D. Loew&quot;. We could not find a syntype neither in the Spinola collection and nor at MNHU. Bohart (in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kimsey, LS" journalOrPublisher="University Press, New York" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" title="The Chrysidid Wasps of the World." year="1991">Kimsey and Bohart 1991</bibRefCitation>
: 491) designated the lectotype based on one specimen from Italy housed in LZM. In 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Dahlbom’s">Dahlbom's</normalizedToken>
collection (LZM), there is one specimen labelled as 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysis aurifrons" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurifrons">Chrysis aurifrons</taxonomicName>
by Dahlbom, but it is not a syntype and it does not bear any lectotype label by Bohart.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
